    "Fears have been expressed over the potential loss of creativity in authors, illustrators and designers, loss of jobs and so forth but this should not sway the thinking of stakeholders.",
    "Machines can never replace the human element required in creative writing, editing, design, marketing, promotion and distribution; they do not have emotions, ethics and moral sense that facilitate the achievement of desired effects in a piece of writing.",
    "The human brain is so complicated that it cannot be replaced by AI; the technology can only complement human efforts.",
    "Publishers in Africa should leverage the affordances of AI to increase efficiency and effectiveness as it reduces the time and cost of production.",
    "It would be beneficial to educational publishers if they adopted AI to quicken the provision and availability of teaching and learning resources to the education sector."
